Aussie Wine Atlas Wine Gift Collection
List.Description:
Grab some mates and taste the best of the land down under with this trio of exceptional Australian wines, including Yalumba FDR1A Cabernet Sauvignon/Shiraz, Langmeil Valley Floor Shiraz and Vasse Felix Cabernet Sauvignon. Produced in the highly acclaimed winegrowing regions of the Barossa Valley and Margaret River, these wines highlight the power and charm of Australian wine.

Wine Gift Trio Includes:

  • Yalumba FDR1A Cabernet Sauvignon/Shiraz
    Founded in 1849, Yalumba is Australia's oldest family-owned winery. Five generations of experience shines through in the FDR (Fine Dry Red) 1A, which is a richly concentrated wine wrapped in a fine package, complete with long, fine grainy tannins.

  • Langmeil Valley Floor Shiraz
    At the heart of the Barossa Valley, lies a rich strip of land exposed to the driest conditions and home to some of the most select Shiraz vineyards in the area. The Langmeil "Valley Floor" Shiraz is full-bodied and mouth-filling, with lovely plums and cherries carried by chocolate and vanillin American oak.

  • Vasse Felix Cabernet Sauvignon
    The long growing seasons, ancient soils and cooling sea breezes make the Margaret River wine region of Western Australia ideal for creating complex and elegant wines. The Vasse Felix Cabernet is rich and seductive, with a mixture of blackcurrant, bay leaf and chocolate dust that bursts to life with tangy, bright acidity.

  • James Halliday's Wine Atlas of Australia

Due to the popularity of this gift, wines or vintages sometimes sell out. Should this happen, we will always substitute with the current vintage and wines with equal or greater value.
